OL,3,GCentral, Tayside & Fife
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA dry morning with plenty of
OL,6,Flong sunny periods. Remaining dry in
OL,7,Fthe afternoon but cloud thickening
OL,8,Fwith more limited brighter spells.
OL,9,FWinds light at first but becoming
OL,10,Fbreezy through the afternoon.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FA cloudy night with rain
OL,13,Fspreading northeastwards, heavy at
OL,14,Ftimes. Rain clearing all but eastern
OL,15,Fcoasts by morning. Winds becoming
OL,16,Fstrong with coastal gales before
OL,17,Feasing later in the night.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
